%% Diagram: Cursor vs Offset pagination — race condition under writes
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant Client
    participant API
    participant DB

    Note over Client,DB: OFFSET pagination — writes shift the window
    Client->>API: GET /feed?offset=40&limit=20
    API->>DB: SELECT ... ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 20 OFFSET 40
    DB-->>API: rows 40..59
    API-->>Client: page 3
    Note over DB: New post inserted at top
    Client->>API: GET /feed?offset=60&limit=20
    API->>DB: SELECT ... LIMIT 20 OFFSET 60
    DB-->>API: rows 60..79 (was 59..78)
    API-->>Client: page 4 — duplicate of last row of page 3

    Note over Client,DB: Cursor (keyset) pagination — stable under writes
    Client->>API: GET /feed?cursor=null
    API->>DB: SELECT ... WHERE (created_at,id) < (max,max) ORDER BY (created_at,id) DESC LIMIT 20
    DB-->>API: 20 rows + nextCursor=(t1,id1)
    API-->>Client: page 1
    Note over DB: New post inserted (any time)
    Client->>API: GET /feed?cursor=(t1,id1)
    API->>DB: SELECT ... WHERE (created_at,id) < (t1,id1) ORDER BY ... LIMIT 20
    DB-->>API: next 20 rows — no overlap, no gap
    API-->>Client: page 2
